<h1>Oh, so you're a programmer now, huh?</h1>

<p>Welcome to programming, the most lucrative career in the world.</p>

<p>Being a programmer means you have now opened up a whole new world of endless
   possibilities.  Instead simply being a passive user of technology, you are
   now a creator.  You can create your own websites, social networks, mobile
   apps, and even games.  You have the ability to create systems and
   environments that can reach potentially millions of people online.  No other
   time in human history has such a thing been possible.  We are truly living in
   the future, my friends, and I am happy to have you be a part of it.</p>

<p>Here are some more benefits of being a programmer:</p>


<table border="black" style="outline:outset; outline-width:10px; outline-color:gray;">
  <tr>
    <th></th>
    <th style="text-align:left;">The Benefits of being a Programmer</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>1</td>
    <td>You get to enjoy a higher than average salary.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>2</td>
    <td>Tech companies provide you free lunch and snacks.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>3</td>
    <td>Software developer jobs are in high demand.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>4</td>
    <td>The ability to work anywhere in the world, so long as you have an
    internet connection.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>5</td>
    <td>Regular people think you're a coputer wizard who is able to conrol
        the Matrix.</td>
  </tr>
</table>


